import{c as e,Q as r,j as n,m as o}from"./chunks/framework.BXc4yaFE.js";const c=JSON.parse('{"title":"+1 for \\"context engineering\\" over \\"prompt engineering\\" — @karpathy","description":"","frontmatter":{"title":"+1 for \\"context engineering\\" over \\"prompt engineering\\" — @karpathy","author":"Andrej Karpathy（@karpathy）","date":"2025-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","source":"https://x.com/karpathy/status/1937902205765607626","type":"tweet"},"headers":[],"relativePath":"research/tweets/2025-06-25-@karpathy-607626.md","filePath":"research/tweets/2025-06-25-@karpathy-607626.md","lastUpdated":1779894392000}'),a={name:"research/tweets/2025-06-25-@karpathy-607626.md"};function i(s,t,l,g,p,d){return r(),n("div",null,[...t[0]||(t[0]=[o('<h1 id="_1-for-context-engineering-over-prompt-engineering-—-karpathy" tabindex="-1">+1 for &quot;context engineering&quot; over &quot;prompt engineering&quot; — @karpathy <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1-for-context-engineering-over-prompt-engineering-—-karpathy" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;+1 for &quot;context engineering&quot; over &quot;prompt engineering&quot; — @karpathy&quot;">​</a></h1><p><strong>來源</strong>：<a href="https://x.com/karpathy/status/1937902205765607626" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">https://x.com/karpathy/status/1937902205765607626</a><strong>作者</strong>：Andrej Karpathy（@karpathy） <strong>發布日期</strong>：2025-06-25 <strong>收錄日期</strong>：2026-04-27 <strong>類型</strong>：推文 <strong>統計</strong>：14353 likes · 2074 retweets · 9185 bookmarks · 2373495 views</p><hr><h2 id="全文" tabindex="-1">全文 <a class="header-anchor" href="#全文" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;全文&quot;">​</a></h2><p>+1 for &quot;context engineering&quot; over &quot;prompt engineering&quot;.</p><p>People associate prompts with short task descriptions you&#39;d give an LLM in your day-to-day use. When in every industrial-strength LLM app, context engineering is the delicate art and science of filling the context window with just the right information for the next step. Science because doing this right involves task descriptions and explanations, few shot examples, RAG, related (possibly multimodal) data, tools, state and history, compacting... Too little or of the wrong form and the LLM doesn&#39;t have the right context for optimal performance. Too much or too irrelevant and the LLM costs might go up and performance might come down. Doing this well is highly non-trivial. And art because of the guiding intuition around LLM psychology of people spirits.</p><p>On top of context engineering itself, an LLM app has to:</p><ul><li>break up problems just right into control flows</li><li>pack the context windows just right</li><li>dispatch calls to LLMs of the right kind and capability</li><li>handle generation-verification UIUX flows</li><li>a lot more - guardrails, security, evals, parallelism, prefetching, ...</li></ul><p>So context engineering is just one small piece of an emerging thick layer of non-trivial software that coordinates individual LLM calls (and a lot more) into full LLM apps. The term &quot;ChatGPT wrapper&quot; is tired and really, really wrong.</p><hr><h2 id="研究摘要" tabindex="-1">研究摘要 <a class="header-anchor" href="#研究摘要" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;研究摘要&quot;">​</a></h2><p><strong>TL;DR</strong>：Context engineering 是工業級 LLM App 的核心技術；精準填充 context window 既是科學也是藝術，「ChatGPT wrapper」的說法嚴重低估其複雜度。</p><h3 id="核心論點" tabindex="-1">核心論點 <a class="header-anchor" href="#核心論點" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;核心論點&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>術語重新定義</strong>：「Prompt engineering」讓人聯想到日常短指令，無法反映生產環境中填充 context window 的技術深度，應改用「context engineering」</li><li><strong>Context 填充是雙刃劍</strong>：太少或格式錯誤 → LLM 無法最優表現；太多或不相關 → 成本上升、效能下降</li><li><strong>Context engineering 的組成元素</strong>：task descriptions、few-shot examples、RAG、多模態資料、tools、state &amp; history、compacting — 必須全部協調好</li><li><strong>LLM App 是更厚的軟體層</strong>：context engineering 只是其中一塊，還需要控制流設計、LLM 路由（能力匹配）、generation-verification UIUX、guardrails、evals、parallelism、prefetching</li><li><strong>「ChatGPT wrapper」是錯誤標籤</strong>：工業強度 LLM App 所需的工程複雜度與一般軟體相當，這個說法已過時且錯誤</li></ul><h3 id="關鍵數據-工具" tabindex="-1">關鍵數據 / 工具 <a class="header-anchor" href="#關鍵數據-工具" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;關鍵數據 / 工具&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>推文獲得 2,373,495 views、14,353 likes、9,185 bookmarks — 說明此觀點引發廣泛共鳴</li><li>引用自 Shopify CEO Tobi Lütke (@tobi) 的原始 context engineering 術語推廣推文</li><li>具體列舉的技術元素：RAG、few-shot、compacting、parallelism、prefetching、evals</li></ul><h3 id="批判性觀察" tabindex="-1">批判性觀察 <a class="header-anchor" href="#批判性觀察" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;批判性觀察&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>論點有充分支撐</strong>：Karpathy 從 OpenAI 創始團隊到 Tesla AI Director 的實際工業經驗背書，論述基於真實生產環境觀察，而非純觀點</li><li><strong>定義邊界略模糊</strong>：「Context engineering」與「LLM orchestration」的邊界在文中未明確區分，這兩個概念在不同社群有時交替使用，可能造成混淆</li><li><strong>對 workspace 的直接應用價值</strong>：本 workspace 的 CLAUDE.md 策略（lazy-load rules、@rules 分層、Skills progressive disclosure）本質上就是 context engineering 的實踐；Karpathy 的框架提供了理論支撐，也驗證了 <code>context-management.md</code> 和 <code>prompt caching</code> 規則設計的正確方向</li></ul><hr><h2 id="評分" tabindex="-1">評分 <a class="header-anchor" href="#評分" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;評分&quot;">​</a></h2><table tabindex="0"><thead><tr><th>維度</th><th>分數</th><th>說明</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>A. Workspace 可行動性 (30%)</td><td>7/10</td><td>驗證了現有 context 管理架構的正確性；可作為 context-management.md 的理論錨點，但不直接產生新 SKILL</td></tr><tr><td>B. 創新性 (20%)</td><td>8/10</td><td>「Context engineering」術語定義清晰且有說服力；對現有術語體系是實質性升級，超越 prompt engineering 的常識認知</td></tr><tr><td>C. 證據品質 (20%)</td><td>6/10</td><td>主要是經驗性論述，無具體 benchmark 數字；但作者本身是強背書，且以 2M+ views 的市場驗證作為佐證</td></tr><tr><td>D. 技術深度 (15%)</td><td>7/10</td><td>清楚列舉了 context 填充的組成要素，LLM App 層次分解具體，工程師可直接參照建立心智模型</td></tr><tr><td>E. 泛化性 (15%)</td><td>9/10</td><td>框架完全通用，適用所有使用 LLM 的工程場景，不限特定工具或平台</td></tr><tr><td><strong>加權總分</strong></td><td><strong>7.35/10</strong></td><td>7×0.3+8×0.2+6×0.2+7×0.15+9×0.15 = 2.1+1.6+1.2+1.05+1.35</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>整合決策</strong>：Rule <strong>理由</strong>：「Context engineering」框架可作為 <code>context-management.md</code> 的概念錨點與術語依據，補強理論基礎而非建立新流程。</p>',22)])])}const u=e(a,[["render",i]]);export{c as __pageData,u as default};
